varies by a factor of two between the solar neighbourhood and a
Galactocentric distance of 12 kpc. Conclusions. We conclude that the
thin disc scale length is in good agreement with the inside-out
formation scenario and that the outer disc is not in dynamical
equilibrium. The warp deformation with time may provide some clues to
