  Abstract                 = {{We discuss the importance of very metal-poor stars to develop an
understanding of the nature of the first stars that formed in the
Universe and the nucleosynthesis events associated with them, as well as
to refine models of galaxy formation, in particular for large spiral
galaxies such as the Milky Way. After briefly reviewing the history of
