the convective envelope of subgiant stars are necessary. Stellar
evolution models can provide us with such predictions, although a
comparision with objects of known age is needed for calibration. Open
clusters are excellent test cases, as they represent a single stellar
population for which the age can be derived through, e.g., isochrone
fitting. In this study, we present a detailed analysis of stars
belonging to the well-known open cluster M67 observed by the APOGEE
survey in the twelfth data release of the Sloan Digital Sky Survey and
