  Year                     = {2016},

  Month                    = mar,

  Abstract                 = {{We examine the distribution of the [O/Fe] abundance ratio in stars
across the Galactic disk using H-band spectra from the Apache Point
Galactic Evolution Experiment (APOGEE). We minimized systematic errors
by considering groups of stars with similar atmospheric parameters. The
APOGEE measurements in the Sloan Digital Sky Survey Data Release 12
reveal that the square root of the star-to-star cosmic variance in
oxygen at a given metallicity is about 0.03-0.04 dex in both the thin
and thick disk. This is about twice as high as the spread found for
solar twins in the immediate solar neighborhood and is probably caused
by the wider range of galactocentric distances spanned by APOGEE stars.
