signal-to-noise values. We confirm an oxygen enhancement in stars of the
thick disk, as has also been seen for other {$\alpha$}-elements. The new
oxygen abundances confirm previous findings for a progressive linear
rise in the oxygen-to-iron ratio with a slope equal to 0.78 from solar
metallicity to [Fe/H] \~{} -1. However, the slope we measured is steeper
