clouds and that of the Galactic disk. Yet limiting the initial abundance
spread in clusters has been hampered by difficulties in obtaining
consistent spectroscopic abundances for different stellar types. Without
reference to any specific model of stellar photospheres, a model for a
homogeneous cluster is that it forms a one-dimensional sequence, with
any differences between members due to variations in stellar mass and
