hypothesis at the level of observed stellar spectra, rather than
constraining homogeneity using derived abundances as is traditionally
done. Using high-resolution APOGEE spectra for 49 giants in M67, NGC
6819, and NGC 2420 I demonstrate that these spectra form one-dimensional
