indications that the asteroseismic scaling relations overestimate the
stellar mass, but we are not yet able to distinguish between different
proposed corrections from the literature. We argue how our ongoing
measurements of more dEBs in more clusters, complemented by dEBs in the
field, should be able to break the degeneracy. We also briefly describe
how we can identify cluster stars that have evolved through non-standard
evolution by making use of ensemble asteroseismology.
