  Author                   = {{Da Costa}, G.~S.},
  Journal                  = {ArXiv e-prints},
  Year                     = {2015},

  Month                    = oct,

  Abstract                 = {{In this contribution the hypothesis that the Galactic globular clusters
with substantial internal [Fe/H] abundance ranges are the former nuclei
of disrupted dwarf galaxies is discussed. Evidence considered includes
the form of the metallicity distribution function, the occurrence of
large diffuse outer envelopes in cluster density profiles, and the
presence of ([s-process/Fe], [Fe/H]) correlations. The hypothesis is
