  Abstract                 = {{The High Efficiency and Resolution Multi-Element spectrograph (HERMES)
currently under construction at the Australian Astronomical Observatory
will be the next major instrument for the Anglo-Australian Telescope. It
will provide a unique and powerful new facility for multi-object
spectroscopy. HERMES uses the 2dF fibre positioning system to provide up
to 392 multiplex capability over a 2 degree field of view. The
spectrograph design includes 4 wavelength channels, each with
VPH-gratings providing a nominal spectral resolving power of 28,000 and
