  Abstract                 = {{Distribution functions (DFs) for dynamically warm thin stellar disks
residing in arbitrary axisymmetric potentials are presented, which
approximately reproduce predescribed surface density and velocity
dispersion profiles. The functional form of the DFs is obtained by
``warming up'' a model made entirely of circular orbits. This can be
done in various ways, giving different functional forms for the DF. In
the best case, the DF reproduces the predescribed profiles to within a
few percent for a typical case reminiscent of the old stellar disk in
the Milky Way. This match may be improved to about 1\% or better by a
