  Volume                   = {572},

  Abstract                 = {{Context. CoRoT and Kepler observations of red giant stars revealed very
rich spectra of non-radial solar-like oscillations. Of particular
interest was the detection of mixed modes that exhibit significant
amplitude, both in the core and at the surface of the stars. It opens
the possibility of probing the internal structure from their innermost
layers up to their surface throughout their evolution on the red giant
branch, as well as on the red clump. <BR /> Aims: Our objective is
primarily to provide physical insight into the mechanism responsible for
