add seven colors to the Cannon model, based on the g, r, i, J, H, K, W1,
and W2 magnitudes from APASS, 2MASS {\amp} WISE, which improves our
constraints on Teff and logg by up to 20\% and on Ak by up to 70\%.
Cross-validation of the model demonstrates that, for high-SNR objects,
our inferred labels agree with the APOGEE values to within 50 K in
temperature, 0.04 magnitudes in Ak, and $\lt$ 0.1 dex in logg, [M/H],
