  Year                     = {2016},

  Month                    = mar,

  Abstract                 = {{This chapter summarizes radio astrometry in relation to current very
long baseline interferometry (VLBI) projects and describes its
perspectives with the SKA. The scientific goals of the astrometry with
the SKA have been discussed in the international and Japanese
communities of researchers, whose major issues are shown here. We have
demonstrated some of the issues, such as censuses of possible targets
and the technical feasibility of astrometry in the SKA frequency bands.
