  Volume                   = {284},

  Abstract                 = {{There is a long term dynamical heating of stellar populations with age
observed in the age velocity dispersion relation (AVR). This effect
allows a determination of the star formation history SFR(t) from local
kinematical data of main sequence stars. Using a self-consistent disk
model for the vertical structure of the disk, we find from the
kinematics of the stars in the solar neighbourhood that the SFR shows a
moderate star burst about 10 Gyr ago followed by a continuous decline to
