h$_{R}$=0.42 R$_{sun}$ and the scale-length of the space
density in the plane (i.e. including the effect of the flare) is H=0.25
R$_{sun}$. The variation of the scale-height due to the flare
follows roughly a law h$_{z}$(R)\~{} h$_{z}$(R$_{sun}$)
exp (R-R$_{sun}$)/([12-0.6R(kpc)] kpc) (for R$\lt$\~{} 15 kpc;
R$_{sun}$=7.9 kpc). The warp moves the mean position of the disc
to a height z$_{w}$=1.2x 10$^{-3}$ R(kpc)$^{5.25}$sin
(phi +5$^{o}$ ) pc (for R$\lt$\~{} 13 kpc; R$_{sun}$=7.9 kpc).
}},
