M$_{&sun;}$). We also compare the predictions of these models with
Kepler observations. For a given {$\Delta$}{$\nu$}, {$\Delta$}{$\Pi$}$_{1}$
depends not only on the stellar mass, but also on mixing processes that
can affect the structure of the core. We find that in the case of more
evolved red-giant-branch stars and regardless of the transport processes
