  Abstract                 = {{Context. Galactic abundance gradients set strong constraints to
chemo-dynamical evolutionary models of the Milky Way. Given the
period-luminosity relations that provide accurate distances and the
large number of spectral lines, Cepheids are excellent tracers of the
present-day abundance gradients. <BR /> Aims: We want to measure the
Galactic abundance gradient of several chemical elements. While the
slope of the Cepheid iron gradient did not vary much from the very first
studies, the gradients of the other elements are not that well
