  Volume                   = {490},

  Abstract                 = {{Context: Classical Cepheids are excellent tracers of intermediate-mass
stars, since their distances can be estimated with very high accuracy.
In particular, they can be adopted to trace the chemical evolution of
the Galactic disk. <BR />Aims: Homogeneous iron abundance measurements
for 33 Galactic Cepheids located in the outer disk together with
