bar`` can be explained by the interaction between the bar and the spiral
arms of the galaxy (Martinez-Valpuesta {\amp} Gerhard 2011). Furthermore
the structural change in the bulge inside l = 4{\deg} measured recently
from VVV data can be explained by the high-density near-axisymmetric
part of the inner boxy bulge (Gerhard {\amp} Martinez-Valpuesta 2012). We
also compare this model with kinematic data from recent spectroscopic
surveys. We use a modified version of the NMAGIC code (de Lorenzi et al.
2007) to study the properties of the Milky Way bar, obtaining an upper
limit for the pattern speed of \~{} 42 km/sec/kpc. See Fig. 1 for a
comparison of one of our best models with BRAVA data (Kunder et al.
2012).
}},
