  Month                    = jul,

  Abstract                 = {{The average bulge [Fe/H] and [Mg/H] are +0.06 and +0.17 dex,
respectively, in Baade's Window, roughly 0.2 dex higher than the thin
disk and \~{}0.7 dex higher than the local thick disk metallicity. This
suggests a higher effective yield in the bulge, perhaps due to more
efficient retention of supernova ejecta. The bulge vertical [Fe/H]
gradient, at \~{}0.5 dex/kpc, appears to be due to a changing mixture of
sub-populations (near +0.3 dex and -0.3 dex and one possibly near -0.7
