relative fractions of MP and MR Cepheids in the 1st and in the 3rd
quadrants differ at the 8{$\sigma$} (MP) and 15{$\sigma$} (MR) levels.
Finally, we found that iron abundances in two local overdensities of the
2nd and of the 4th quadrant cover individually a range in iron abundance
of {\ap}0.5 dex. <BR />Conclusions: Current findings indicate that the
recent chemical enrichment across the Galactic disk shows a clumpy
distribution.

