characteristic radial extent of HVCs of R $_{halo}$ \~{} 50 kpc, a
total H I mass in HVCs of \~{}10$^{8}$ M $_{&sun;}$, and a
neutral-gas accretion rate of \~{}0.7 M $_{&sun;}$ yr$^{-1}$
for M31/Milky-Way-type galaxies. Using a Holmberg-like luminosity
scaling of the halo size of galaxies we estimate R $_{halo}$ \~{} 110
