HVCs at z {\ap} 0 most likely is dominated by galaxies with total H I
masses between 10$^{8.5}$ and 10$^{10}$ M $_{&sun;}$.
Our model indicates that the H I disks of galaxies and their surrounding
HVC population can account for 30\%-100\% of intervening QSO
absorption-line systems with log N(H I) {\gt}= 17.5 at z {\ap} 0. We
