fall well inside the observational MW range. (c) We measure the
disk-to-total ratio kinematically and find that D/T = 0.42. (d) The
cold-gas fraction and star formation rate at z = 0, on the other hand,
fall short of the values estimated for the MW. As a first scientific
exploitation of the simulation series, we study the spatial distribution
of hot X-ray luminous gas. We have found that most of this X-ray
emitting gas is in a halo-like distribution accounting for an important
fraction but not all of the missing baryons. An important amount of hot
gas is also present in filaments. In all our models there is not a
