inherent to past Bayesian approaches, lead to deviations of several
standard deviations and unreliable errors on the same data. By its
flexibility and the simultaneous analysis of multiple independent
measurements for a star, it will be ideal to analyse and cross-calibrate
the large ongoing and forthcoming surveys, like Gaia-European Southern
Observatory (ESO), SDSS, Gaia and LSST.
