kinematically subclassified in samples of thick disk, thin disk, and
intermediate stellar populations. All sample stars show solar {$\alpha$}-Fe
ratios, and most of them are old and still quite metal rich. The orbits
suggest that the thin disk, thick disk and intermediate populations were
formed at Galactocentric distances of \~{}8 kpc, \~{}6 kpc, and \~{}7 kpc,
