  Abstract                 = {{Context. Solar twins are stars with similar stellar (surface) parameters
to the Sun that can have a wide range of ages. This provides an
opportunity to analyze the variation of their chemical abundances with
age. Nissen (2015, A{\amp}A, 579, A52) recently suggested that the
