diffusion, which accounts for errors of about 3.7\% and 1.5\% on mass and
radius. The cumulative effects of the considered uncertainty sources can
produce biased estimates of stellar characteristics. Comparison of the
results of our technique with other grid techniques shows that the
systematic biases induced by the differences in the estimation grids are
generally greater than the statistical errors involved.

Appendix A, Table 1, Figs. 6, 8-11, 13, 14 are available in electronic
