and M$_{Ks}$, 0.1 dex for [Fe/H], [C/H] and [N/H], and better than
0.05 dex for [{$\alpha$}/M] ([{$\alpha$}/Fe]). The results are satisfactory
even for a spectral SNR of 20. The work presents first determinations of
[C/H] and [N/H] abundances from a vast data set of LAMOST, and, to our
knowledge, the first reported implementation of absolute magnitude
estimation directly based on a vast data set of observed spectra. The
derived stellar parameters for millions of stars from the LAMOST surveys
will be publicly available in the form of value-added catalogues.
